					<description><![CDATA[<p>Click Therapeutics Inc. said Boehringer Ingelheim, one of the world&#8217;s largest pharmaceutical companies, has led a $50 million Series D strategic investment round. However, a shift in command is clear,</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/click-therapeutics-secures-50m-series-d-funding-deal/" data-wpel-link="internal">Click Therapeutics Secures $50M Series D Funding Deal</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.clicktherapeutics.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Click Therapeutics Inc.</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> said Boehringer Ingelheim, one of the world&#8217;s largest pharmaceutical companies, has led a $50 million Series D strategic </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/milltech-bags-60m-to-scale-treasury-and-fx-tools/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">investment </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. </span>However, a shift in command is clear, as Click Therapeutics would now assume responsibility for leading the commercial launch of CT-155. The $50 million financing plus additional funding to support commercialization is tailored to accelerate the regulatory process of CT-155.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Strategic Pivot in Commercialization</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Since 2020, Click and Boehringer Ingelheim have collaborated to bring CT-155 to market. In this new deal, Boehringer Ingelheim is ceding complete product responsibility (including all commercial and marketing authorization rights) to Click Therapeutics.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_199802" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199802" class="size-large wp-image-199802" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/click_therapeutics-1536x438-1-1024x292.jpg" alt="click therapeutics logo" width="1024" height="292" /><p id="caption-attachment-199802" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Click Therapeutics </p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This is a significant milestone for Click, which is transitioning from a pure R&amp;D partner to an integrated commercial stage powerhouse. David Benshoof Klein, CEO and founder of Click Therapeutics, said:</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Boehringer Ingelheim&#8217;s choice of Click to deliver CT-155 to patients is an incredible validation of the vision we have spent ten years developing and our executional capabilities. We are ready now to step up and are laser-focused on getting this FDA-designated Breakthrough Device to patients.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:</span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/milltech-bags-60m-to-scale-treasury-and-fx-tools/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400"> MillTech Bags $60M to Scale Treasury and FX Tools</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Breakthrough Data Driving the Investment</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series D is following the completion of the Phase III CONVOKE study. The trial evaluated CT-155 as an add-on to antipsychotic drugs, which are standard treatment for schizophrenia. The results achieved will be historic, as this was the first pivotal trial of a digital therapeutic to demonstrate a statistically significant reduction in the experiential negative symptoms of schizophrenia (social withdrawal, apathy, and lack of motivation). </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Relative to a digital control group, the study experienced a 62% relative improvement in symptom severity at 16 weeks. The therapy was also tolerated well, and no app-related discontinuations occurred, whereas the usual drugs in this patient population are associated with a harsh side effect profile.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strengthening a Dominant Pipeline</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment of 50 million dollars shows a potential high-water mark for Click Therapeutics. In just 24 months, Click Therapeutics has gained several major milestones:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Rejoyn&#x2122; (co-developed with Otsuka Pharmaceuticals) obtained an FDA authorization and became a digital treatment for Major Depressive Disorder (MDD).</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">The FDA cleared a new digital therapeutic named CT-132 in 2025, for the preventive treatment of episodic migraine.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400">Click partnered with Ultrahuman for wearable biomarkers for migraine and secured a Series C investment round with Medidata/Dassault Systèmes.</li>
</ul>
<p>With rights and funding to acquire CT-155, cementing its role as the “operating system” for “Software Enhanced Drug&#x2122;” therapies.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Road Ahead</span></h2>
<p>Although the digital therapeutics industry has been smooth sailing, Click&#8217;s platform-first approach shows they are the tactic to beat. If approved, the new drug will be the latest addition to Click&#8217;s portfolio that marries chemistry and behavioural software into treatment tools.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/click-therapeutics-secures-50m-series-d-funding-deal/" data-wpel-link="internal">Click Therapeutics Secures $50M Series D Funding Deal</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
