					<description><![CDATA[<p>Record Fundraising and Investor Confidence Court Square Capital Partners, a prominent U.S. middle market private equity firm has announced the final closing of its Fund V at the hard cap</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/court-square-capital-3-8b/" data-wpel-link="internal">Court Square Capital Raises $3.8B to Expand Middle Market Investments</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Record Fundraising and Investor Confidence</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Court Square Capital Partners, a prominent U.S. middle market private equity firm has announced the final closing of its Fund V at the hard cap with $3.8 billion in total capital commitments, surpassing its target of $3.0 billion.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The closing reflects continued investor confidence in Court Square’s differentiated strategy and proven track record. The firm had significant demand, resulting in its largest capital raise to date, from both existing long-standing relationships as well as new global investors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fund V saw over 40 new investors join, from more than 20 countries. The investor base includes prominent pensions, asset managers, insurance companies and family offices. The firm is the largest investor in its funds with the general partner committing significant capital.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“This close signals strong support for our approach,” said Chris Bloise, President and Managing Partner. “We are excited about the opportunities across our target sectors and look forward to partnering with founders and management teams to drive long-term growth.”</span></p>
<h2><b>Strategic Focus Across Core Sectors</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fund V is focusing on control buyouts in business services, healthcare, industrials, and technology. The fund has also done six deals already so there is a good momentum there. Rick Walsh, Partner at Court Square, underlined the firm’s 47-year track record. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“Our emphasis on investor alignment and co-investment alongside our investors has consistently delivered strong performance,” Walsh said during his spotlight session. He highlighted the firm’s DPI story, noting that Court Square returned $7.4 billion from 17 full exits and 15 dividend recaps since 2022.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Court Square is looking to build on the momentum of Fund IV, which invested in 23 companies within the firm’s core sectors. Over its history dating back to 1979, Court Square has deployed over $13.4 billion across more than 245 investments. The firm’s strategy centers around partnering with founders, families and management teams to grow these industry leading companies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The disciplined process guarantees that each portfolio company is provided the operational support, the access to capital and the strategic guidance necessary by Court Square to enhance its market position in addition to creating long-term vаluе for investors.</span></p>
<h2><b>Global Participation and Institutional Alignment<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_199766" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199766" class="size-full wp-image-199766" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-elem_Nxji5oAASWq_u85Mw4eOsg_uF7_Dqf2RHS9EphP_vcJcQ_cover.png" alt="Global institutional investors backing Court Square’s fund with strong governance and long-term investment strategy." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-199766" class="wp-caption-text">Court Square attracts global institutional capital, reinforcing investor confidence in its disciplined and strategic investment approach. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The fifth fund raised capital from both existing and new investors. In total, more than 40 institutions coming from 20 different countries decided to trust the firm’s vision by allocating resources. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Among these, there were pension funds, insurance companies, asset managers all sharing a common interest for </span><a href="https://www.global-solutions-initiative.org/article/the-case-for-sustainable-value-creation/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">sustainable value creation</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> on the long run. The fund shows that Court Square can draw investor interest in a tough market. The firm’s approach, which includes sector knowledge and a GP co-investment, has helped set it apart.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Kirkland &amp; Ellis LLP provided legal counsel to the fund. Raymond James Private Capital Advisory and HMC Global served as placement agents. Court Square’s success in securing capital from international investors is a strong vote of confidence in the firm’s governance, investment discipline, and long-term vision.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/certifid-raises-47-5m/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">CertifID Raises $47.5M To Strengthen Real Estate Fraud Protection</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Long-Term Vision and Market Impact</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Court Square is still focusing on investments that have sustainable growth. This V fund will invest in sectors that have a strong secular and chances to make operational improvement.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The firm is focused on a partnership approach and recognizes that long-term value creation depends on robust relationships within the investment community, as well as with company founders and management teams. This partnership strategy, together with Court Square’s considerable experience in operational improvements, market expansion and strategic repositioning, has allowed many portfolio companies to achieve exceptional results.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With $10.1 billion of assets under management as of December 2015, the firm has considerable resources to invest in transactions across multiple sectors and geographic markets. Court Square uses the significant experience and contacts of its partners to identify suitable investment opportunities in target middle market companies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors are more and more in demand of such kind of private equity firms which could provide not only the knowledge of the sector but also its practical appliance. The Court Square’s concept to make a single whole out of a strategic control and a long-term partnership is what they want.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The oversubscription of the fund and the significant GP commitment meant that there was a strong demand from investors to become part of the new fund. Both old and new investors participating in it is an external validation to the firm on their approach and long future.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/court-square-capital-3-8b/" data-wpel-link="internal">Court Square Capital Raises $3.8B to Expand Middle Market Investments</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
